This adds a new unit test that makes sure that there are no overlapping file extension patterns in any of the syntaxes.

For a few known exceptions, we also add tests to make sure that they are mapped to the right syntax. Some of these tests currently fail. I'm not yet sure how to fix this:
```rust
     assert_eq!(test.syntax_name("test.sass"), "Sass");
    // TODO: make these tests pass:
    // assert_eq!(test.syntax_name("test.h"), "C");
    // assert_eq!(test.syntax_name("test.hs"), "Haskell (Improved)");
    // assert_eq!(test.syntax_name("test.js"), "JavaScript (Babel)"); 
```

Just a few small things that I thought about after looking how the new templates look like on GitHub.

The main change is that I made the "header" section into a HTML comment. This way, users will not have to remove the header part.

@eth-p What do you think?
